Should the standard client info properties sent to server and made visible in DCS Web GUI too

Changes Look good. It is good to see exception is being changed to passing error via return code because Trafodion has rarely used exception concepts. It makes it less confusing in Trafodion code base.

I have comment on the usage of assert in some of the methods called in by this change like ComUser::getCurrentUser.  The assert API may be no-op in Trafodion because some of the cpp file and Makefile used in Trafodion sets in the macro NDEBUG. This can cause non-deterministic behavior when these methods relies on assert but it becomes no-op.
I will look at the use of assert and return internal error, when it make sense.  Thanks for the info.

This change requires a metadata upgrade.  I am not sure when we are planning to do a Trafodion metadata upgrade.  We have several things that we want to include when a metadata upgrade does occurs and therefore, we should do them all at once.  Until we decide when the metadata upgrade occurs, I don't think this fix can be delivered.  I made a suggestion as part of comments in CmpSeabaseDDLmd file that will allow this change to be delivered without a metadata upgrade.
